---
By: Ingmar Bergman
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 337
    Verse: 4
Tags:
  - Senility is not confined to old
---
Old age is the climbing of a mountain. The higher you get, the more tired
and breathless you become. But your view becomes much more extensive.
